@node "useage" "RentSpace - Using the Editor"

* The Main Menu:
----------------
  E> Enter a NEW advert     This takes you to the editor window where ANSI
                            text is added.
  V> View Current Advert    This views the Current Advert (if there is one)
                            and displays it.
  A> About                  Brings up the About screen displays a bit about
                            the Program and Which BBS the program has been
                            FREELY Registered to.
  Q> Return to the BBS      Quit's the Editor Program, and returns you to
                            the BBS.

* Adding coloured text lines:
-----------------------------
To add different colours to the display, use the guide on screen to get the
desired colour, you must enter some text before you can get to enter a
colour, or enter a SLASH DOT " /. " for a blank line (read below for more on
the SLASH DOT)

* centering the text:
---------------------
To center the text in the final output file just follow the on screen
instructions, there is also an on screen function for Normal (Dull) colours
or Bold (Bright) colours... This was added on request...

* To get a blank line using the DOT:
------------------------------------
Placing a SLASH DOT " /. " will cause the program to produce a blank line
a SLASH DOT combined with other text like : " /. hello " or " /.hello "
will not produce a blank line...
Also you must Press return 3 times after you have entered your text...
ie, don't enter any colours or try to center the text, just the return key
needs to be pressed, you'll know when you have it right because the words
blank line... will get printed to the screen...
if you do make the mistake of entering the colour number or centering it
then garbage will get printed instead of the correct stuff.
The Words  " blank line.... " should appear to state that it is one....
but the words will not be in the final output file. ;^)

* Exit without saving file:
---------------------------
To exit without saving the entered advert type " /Q or /q " at the start of
any new line. Pressing return on a blank line brings up a Question asking if
you want to save this data...
@endnode

@node "inst" "RentSpace Installation"

Start out by first creating a directory in your DOORS: path called
  - RentSpace

Copy archive contents into this directory.....
Other files needed will be created by the program....

* Creating a menu function in MAX'sBBS like this for the Editor:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

key:     Function:   Extra  Lo acc:    Hi acc     Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 R        34         0      10000      10000      Doors:RentSpace/RentSpace

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Set this so only Sysop can access it, this is to stop callers from
destroying current advertisements.  This way a caller has to ask the sysop
if he/she can leave an advert.......

   WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING

The reason this Door is placed under SYSOP only control is because ALL auto
inserts that MAX'sBBS translates are insertable ie %X = Forced Hangup
which can be hazzardous to the next caller... however if a caller does add
a %X they will be Disconnected... Because the program automatically adds
Colour to the text and re-inserts the text, causeing the AutoInsert to
Activate... Please try this using %f = callers full name...

   WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING - WARNING

* The Viewer:
-------------
Edit the file MainDoor.text, adding this line into the file,

RentSpace/RentSpaceV

This will display the advert everytime a caller logs in.......Simple ;^)
it will automatically exit if the file to display in not found...
@endnode

