@node "cust" "Customizing the editor"

* Customizing the editor to your BBS:
-------------------------------------
I can customize the editor to suit your BBS, Just send details and info to
the e-mail address under Contacting the Author...

* things I will need to customize the editor to your BBS:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Your own Ansi Screen for Display    This will be built into the program,
                                    (optional)
Your BBS Name                       This will be built into the program,
                                    and LOCKED in place (ie, Tamper Proof).
Your Real Name and BBS line Number  Only if New Zealand resident and a
                                    MAXsBBS Sysop
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Any other problem's, bug reports, etc.. can be directed to me at the e-mail
address under Contacting the Author.
If you find this Guide hard to understand then please play with the programs
you never know they might actually teach you by playing with them.

                 8^) Smile it ain't that bad, is it?? (^8

                            Enjoy the Programs

@endnode

@node "brif" "A Brief History"

* A Brief History:
------------------

1.0b  Beta version sent to testers, Trial and error version.

1.2b  Beta version sent to testers after bug in ANSI output file was fixed
      also fixed a bug in Main Editor screen which caused the program to
      lock up on occasion, also didn't Output 16 colour ANSI correctly, bug
      put aside until I get around to fixing it.
      Freeware version.

1.3   ** First Public Release **
      HardCoded BBS name into the Program code, makes it Tamper Proof.
      Program will fail to work if HEXEdited...
      Updated the Editor so it is easier to read on all 8 colour ANSI
      displays.
      ANSI Bug Fixed - Now Outputs a 16 colour ANSI Advert file.
      Cleaned up the code a little, so as I might be able to understand my
      own coded material ;^)
      And it's still FREEWARE ;^)

1.3a  Updated the program, found a few errors within my own code...
      also fixed a few ansi errors... these didn't effect the output in
      any way, but made the program look Ikky from a terminal...
      Added anti-lockup routine, supplyed by Randy Quick...

2.0b  Update and Enhanced version
      Add an Option for the user to center the text in the output file via
      a Yes/No Question...
      Also added extra colours option for final output file... this too is
      under a Yes/No type question...
      Gave the Program an All purpose output file... thus not left with the
      Ugly 3D one it started life with... This new one is much nicer...
      Made the Editor screen less croweded...

2.1   Update and bug fix... yup found 1 little bug, well not actually a bug
      just an oversite... I missed the colour number 30 Dark Grey...
      replaced the DOT command with a SLASH DOT " /. " instead of just a DOT
      Yes, It still is Freeware... So go on Share it about Free of charge...

2.1a  Small Enhancement in the code, also made the executable a bit smaller.

2.2   Final Release, Executable a bit larger due to ansi upgrade...
      Project enhancement of Ansi Only

@endnode
